{
    "id": "284",
    "title": "Precision Medicine for Cardiomyopathy (PRIMaCY) Score",
    "desc": "The Precision Medicine for Cardiomyopathy (PRIMaCY) Score predicts sudden cardiac death (SCD) risk in pediatric patients with hypertrophic cardiomyopathy (HCM).",
    "data": {
        "orgreference": [
            {
                "href": "https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/32418493/",
                "text": "Miron A, Lafreniere-Roula M, Steve Fan CP, et al. A validated model for sudden cardiac death risk prediction in pediatric hypertrophic cardiomyopathy. Circulation. 2020;142(3):217-229."
            }
        ],
        "other_refer": [],
        "evidence": "<p>Risk is calculated using the clinical/genetic model from <a href=\"https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/32418493/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Miron 2020</a> with the following variables:</p>\n<ul>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\"><span>Age, years.</span></p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\"><span>Height, cm.</span></p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\"><span>Weight, kg.</span></p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\"><span>Maximum interventricular septal diameter, mm.</span></p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\"><span>Maximum left ventricular (LV) posterior wall diameter, mm.</span></p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\"><span>Left atrial (LA) diameter at end-systole, mm.</span></p>\n<ul>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\">See <a href=\"https://cdn-web-img.mdcalc.com/content/Determination-of-left-atrial-diameter-for-PRIMaCY-study-patients.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">here</a> for details on how to measure.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\"><span>Peak LV outflow tract gradient, mmHg.</span></p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\"><span>History of non-sustained ventricular tachycardia (NVT) in prior 6 months (yes or no).</span></p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\"><span>History of unexplained syncope in prior 6 months (yes or no).</span></p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\"><span>Genotype status (not tested or tested).</span></p>\n<ul>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"2\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\"><span>If tested, mutation (negative, positive, or variant of uncertain significance).</span></p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>",
        "facts": "<p>Categorical predictors of 5-year SCD risk (only relevant to patients with these risk factors):</p>\n<table style=\"width: 100%; height: 54.7968px; border-width: 1px; border-style: none;\"><colgroup><col style=\"width: 50.1253%;\"><col style=\"width: 50.1253%;\"></colgroup>\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 22.3984px;\">\n<td style=\"height: 22.3984px;\"><strong>Predictor</strong></td>\n<td style=\"height: 22.3984px;\"><strong>Hazard Ratios [95% CI]</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 22.3984px;\">\n<td style=\"height: 22.3984px;\">Prior history of NVT</td>\n<td style=\"height: 22.3984px;\">2.87 [1.00, 6.57]</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 10px;\">\n<td style=\"height: 10px;\">Prior history of syncope</td>\n<td style=\"height: 10px;\">7.40 [1.21, 32.81]</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p></p>\n<table style=\"width: 100%; height: 246.382px; border-width: 1px; border-style: none;\"><colgroup><col style=\"width: 50%;\"><col style=\"width: 50%;\"></colgroup>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td><img src=\"https://s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/cdn-web-img.mdcalc.com/content/PRIMaCY/FIG3A.jpg\" width=\"100%\"></td>\n<td><img src=\"https://s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/cdn-web-img.mdcalc.com/content/PRIMaCY/FIG3B.jpg\" width=\"100%\"></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><img src=\"https://s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/cdn-web-img.mdcalc.com/content/PRIMaCY/FIG3C.jpg\" width=\"100%\"></td>\n<td><img src=\"https://s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/cdn-web-img.mdcalc.com/content/PRIMaCY/FIG3D.jpg\" width=\"100%\"></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><img src=\"https://s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/cdn-web-img.mdcalc.com/content/PRIMaCY/FIG3E.jpg\" width=\"100%\"></td>\n<td></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><img src=\"https://s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/cdn-web-img.mdcalc.com/content/PRIMaCY/FIG3F.jpg\" width=\"100%\"></td>\n<td><img src=\"https://s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/cdn-web-img.mdcalc.com/content/PRIMaCY/FIG3G.jpg\" width=\"100%\"></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>From <a href=\"https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/32418493/\">Miron 2020</a>.</p>",
